      "narrative": "# CORRUPTION BRIEF: Boeing / NASA Contract Awards\n\n**The Boeing Company (BA) has received two NASA contracts totaling approximately $32.9 billion** — a $22.4 billion award and a $10.5 billion award — representing one of the largest dual-contract stacking arrangements in recent federal aerospace procurement history.\n\n**Boeing maintains extensive lobbying infrastructure and direct relationships with members of the Senate Commerce Committee and House Appropriations subcommittees** that oversee NASA's budget authorization, with documented campaign contributions to members holding direct oversight authority over these contract approvals.\n\n**These awards follow a documented pattern of Boeing receiving major federal contracts during periods of concurrent regulatory scrutiny** — including ongoing FAA investigations into 737 MAX and 787 manufacturing defects — raising documented questions about the relationship between federal contract flow and regulatory forbearance, a pattern previously reported by ProPublica, The Seattle Times, and the Government Accountability Office.\n\n**Boeing has faced at least three Inspector General reviews since 2019 related to cost overruns and performance failures on NASA's Space Launch System**, for which it has nonetheless continued to receive contract modifications and extensions totaling billions in additional federal funds.\n\n---\n\n⚠️ *This brief is based on publicly available procurement records and reported facts. It does not constitute financial advice. The algorithmic \"buy signal\" framing in the source data reflects a trading model, not editorial judgment.*"
